American-Senegelese music star Akon has urged anyone who “wants to enjoy life” to come to Africa. According to him, investors can get the best deals on the continent. The ‘Mr. Lonely’ crooner stated this in a post on his Facebook page following a visit to Uganda.   No plans to increase telecoms tariff, says NCC     FG approves interventions for tertiary institutions     Supreme Court upholds Rivers’ claim to 17 oil wells in…   The post showed five pictures of the musician-turned entrepreneur in a white African outfit, popularly known as “Senators” in Nigeria. Akon is known to have several business interests in America and across Africa, including Uganda. “There’s no deals like the deals cut in Africa. Do you want to enjoy life? Come home!!!!!” the post reads.